title: For Sale:  Rockola m1 carbine
postcontent:
Rockola m1 carbine Post war upgrades Is import marked blue sky (don't email me complaining that it's a blue sky and has a shot out Barrel look at the picture I wouldn't buy a carbine or any firearm with a shot out barrel)the Korean war to its History Is a mixmaster has gone through atleast 2 arsenal rebuilds No low balling Don't like my price thats fine make me a reaonable  offer Partial trades are acceptable with cash on your side 

My feelings on As Delivered to the Military, verses Mix-master M1 and M1 Carbines.If you want a War Relic, you want a Mix-Master. I can say with certainty, that 99% of any of these rifles that served in Combat, will be a Mix-Master. There were a very high number of these that were mixmasters when delivered to the Military to meet production requirements, and were surely made into mix-masters during group cleanings and repairs. All of theses that were returned, inspected and repaired for reuse or resale, were future disassembled and repaired.The only ones that did not go through this process, were either presentation ones, or non issued ones. Even the Non Combat ones that were used in the States for Training, were dissembled and mixed.If you are buying a War Relic, it will be a Mixmaster, or a rifle that someone destroyed the history, and Made it All "Correct".My feelings: I would much rather have a True War Relic, that had seen battle, went through rebuild, and had the needed improvements done to it, than a recreated All Original.Inland front sight (n)Sa amco bayonet lug trigger housing Winchester (w)Winchester push safety (ew)Underwood bolt (.u.)Inland trigger  (ri)IBM hammer (wmb)Type 4 or 5 mag catch (m)Slide 2 or 3 IBM  (aob)Trigger marked inland (RI on top )WILL NOT SHIP DON'T EVEN ASK Colt 1903M1 garandGlock 21 Walther SteyrBeretta DpmsGlock 27Glock 33

The FX-9 pistol (Freedom Xtreme-9mm pistol) has a familiar set of operating controls for the avid AR-15 user, it accepts AR-15 stocks / braces and buffer tube assemblies,as well as most free float AR-15 rail assemblies.

The FX-9  comes standard with a 33 rd double stack Glock® style 9mm  magazine. When we designed the FX-9 our goals were Reliability , Affordability, and familiar controls for the user.

The FX-9 is machined from billet material, anodized type III aluminum components . Steel components are full hard nitride and nickle boron nitirded including the barrel,bolt,ejector,last round hold open,feed ramp and extractor for extended wear properties and corrosion resistance.

The upper and lower receiver are more than 1.00″ shorter than a standard AR-15 upper and lower receiver making it more compact and lighter than a standard mil-spec AR-15 design.

Features Include-

LIMITED LIFE TIME WARRANTY

-Chambered in 9×19

-KAK Stabilizing Arm Brace
-AR-15 Configured Rear charging handle
-AR-15 Configured safety selector
-AR-15 Configured last round bolt hold open
-AR-15 Configured magazine release
-AR-15 Compatible pistol grips (without the rear tang)
– 3″ Muzzle Enhancer (suppressor look alike)
-compatible with 9mm approved 1/2″x 28 T.P.I. muzzle devices and suppressors
-compatible with KNS precision® AR-15 trigger pins. 

We do not recommend using aftermarket lighter weight triggers, if you wish to try an aftermarket trigger group we recommend keeping your factory supplied trigger group nearby for re-installation as it has more disconnector engagement built into it than a normal mil spec trigger group or after market trigger group  .

The FX-9 upholds Xtreme reliability with a wide range of ammo including many hollow point designs for self defense and full metal jacket .

We do not recommend the use of non jacketed ammunition as unprotected lead can cause fouling and buildups that plated and jacketed bullets do not.



Do Not use aluminum case ammunition in your FX-9 !!

 -115 gr. FMJ Tulammo®

title: For Sale/Trade:  Tristar l-120
postcontent: I have a tristar l-120 in very good condition for sale or trade. It comes with a hard plastic lockable case and 2 magazines. One 17 rnd and one 19 rnd extended. This is an awesome copy of a cz-75 but has an alloy frame which makes it quite a bit lighter. The slide rides inside the frame allowing for a more solid lockup and lower bore axis.Its probably seen 250-300 rnds in its lifetime. Has a little bit of finish wear on the outside of the barrel and a crack in the factory grip which has been repaired but could easily take cz-75 grips with a little fitment. The barrels on tristars/canicks are chrome lined and can handle +p rounds no problem. It has been 100% reliable not one fte or ftf the whole time. Its taken several different brands and loadings and functions flawlessly.These pistols will take cz-75 magazines and they function as they should so magazines shouldn't be a problem. I just use the mec-gar ones that they come with but tried my actual cz-75 mags in it with no problem. The mec-gar mags are pretty cheap around $20 or so. I have always had good experience with them.

title: For Sale:  1884 Springfield Trapdoor
postcontent: This is a Model 1884 US Springfield single shot Trapdoor 45/70 rifle.  It was manufactured in 1890; serial #435123. The rifle is in remarkable shape for being over 120 years old. The blueing has all turned to a gray patina and there is no color case hardening visable on the lock or side plates. There is no rust visable on this gun. The bore is bright and clean.  The rifle still retains the original Buffington, elevator rear sight which is worth around $225 by itself.  The rifle shoots the 405 grain bullet commonaly known as the 45/70 Government load available at any good sports store. This rifle can be used to hunt any game animal that walks on the North American continent. This rifle was sporterized at some point; barrel cut to 23"; Sears Robuck sold these in their catalog in 1900 for $2.50 each! It has two small pieces of wood missing next to the tang but nowhere else.Is a great gun to hang above the fireplace or lots of fun to shoot.Earlier percushion versions of this rifle saw use during the Civil War. This model also saw action with Custer during his last stand and neumerous other indian campaigns in the 1890s.  Also was used during the Spanish American war and the Phillipine American war.Own a true piece of American History!  $400 Cash or Best OfferIllinois buyer must have valid FOID.
